&lt;li&gt;Work with Marketing to ensure educational content aligns with our brand and messaging.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Design and manage a customer certification program, including assessments, credentialing, and renewal.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Partner with Customer Success Operations to connect learning data with customer health metrics.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Establish content governance processes to keep learning materials accurate and up to date.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Measure program effectiveness using learner engagement, course completion, certification, and adoption metrics.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What You&#39;ll Bring&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;3–6 years of experience in customer education, instructional design, technical writing, or learning and development within a B2B SaaS environment.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong instructional design and technical writing skills, with the ability to simplify complex product concepts into clear, engaging learning experiences.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience creating multi-format learning content, including written documentation, e-learning courses, videos, and reference materials.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience with an LMS or course authoring platform such as Articulate 360, Skilljar, Thought Industries, or Docebo.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong cross-functional collaboration skills with Product, Customer Success, and Marketing.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Excellent written and verbal communication skills.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;A builder mindset with the ability to thrive in a fast-paced, evolving environment and work independently.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience in industrial technology, manufacturing, or another highly technical SaaS environment is a plus.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
